            "examples": [
                {
                    "id": "default_run_24h",
                    "description": "24-hour integration of the 819-reaction GEOS-Chem fullchem mechanism from a polluted-urban initial state (T=298 K, num_density=40.9 mol/m^3, NO=10 ppb, NO2=20 ppb, ISOP=2 ppb, O3=70 ppb) with constant noon-rate NO2 photolysis (j_11=0.0149 1/s). Plots O3, NO, NO2 and OH vs time over the full diurnal window. After mdl-5xp routed render_example_plots through earthsci_toolkit.simulation.simulate (the canonical Python ESS runner), LSODA on the cse-compiled rhs handles the 24-h window in ~3-4 min wall on the workspace machine after the per-component compile cache (~80-130 s) is warm; the integrator's adaptive timestep grows large once the HOx/NOx cycle reaches its photostationary balance, so wall cost grows sub-linearly with window length.",
                    "time_span": {
                        "start": 0,
                        "end": 86400
                    },
                    "initial_state": {
                        "type": "per_variable",
                        "values": {
                            "NO": 10,
                            "NO2": 20,
                            "O3": 70,
                            "ISOP": 2,
                            "OH": 4e-06,
                            "HO2": 4e-06,
                            "SO2": 1e-09,
                            "SALAAL": 1e-09,
                            "SALCAL": 1e-09
                        }
                    },
                    "parameters": {
                        "T": 298.0,
                        "num_density": 40.896894217403165,
                        "j_11": 0.0149
                    },
                    "plots": [
                        {
                            "id": "O3_vs_time",
                            "type": "line",
                            "description": "O3 over 24 h of polluted-urban photochemistry under constant-noon photolysis. Initial fast drift settles into a slow net production driven by VOC (ISOP) oxidation; the diurnal-mean drift is the canonical signature of a stand-alone fullchem run with no diurnally-varying j-rates.",
                            "x": {
                                "variable": "t",
                                "label": "time (s)"
                            },
                            "y": {
                                "variable": "O3",
                                "label": "O3 (ppb)"
                            }
                        },
                        {
                            "id": "NO_vs_time",
                            "type": "line",
                            "description": "NO over 24 h \u2014 NO2+hv\u2192NO+O3P competes against NO+O3\u2192NO2 and NO+HO2/RO2 pathways; the NO/NO2 partition equilibrates fast and then drifts with the slower O3 budget.",
                            "x": {
                                "variable": "t",
                                "label": "time (s)"
                            },
                            "y": {
                                "variable": "NO",
                                "label": "NO (ppb)"
                            }
                        },
                        {
                            "id": "NO2_vs_time",
                            "type": "line",
                            "description": "NO2 over 24 h \u2014 depleted by photolysis, replenished by NO+O3 and HO2/RO2+NO; the partner of the NO trace under the fast NOx photostationary cycle.",
                            "x": {
                                "variable": "t",
                                "label": "time (s)"
                            },
                            "y": {
                                "variable": "NO2",
                                "label": "NO2 (ppb)"
                            }
                        },
                        {
                            "id": "OH_vs_time",
                            "type": "line",
                            "description": "OH over 24 h \u2014 sits in the HOx photostationary state set by the j_11/O3/H2O budget on a sub-second timescale, then drifts with the slow O3/HCHO/CO budgets over the diurnal window.",
                            "x": {
                                "variable": "t",
                                "label": "time (s)"
                            },
                            "y": {
                                "variable": "OH",
                                "label": "OH (ppb)"
                            }
                        }
                    ]
                },
                {
                    "id": "jNO2_photolysis_sweep",
                    "description": "NO2-photolysis sensitivity at fixed polluted-urban initial composition (T=298 K, NO=10 ppb, NO2=20 ppb, ISOP=2 ppb, O3=70 ppb). Sweeps j_11 (the GEOS-Chem j-table index for NO2+hv \u2192 NO + O3P, see GasChem.jl/src/geoschem_fullchem.jl:3014) from dark (0 s^-1) through bright noon (~0.02 s^-1) on the same 8-grid superfast uses, integrates each grid point for 1800 s (30 min \u2014 long enough that the slow O3 budget responds to the sweep), then plots the t=1800 s OH and O3 against j_11. The HOx subsystem equilibrates on \u226a 1 s and OH tracks the photostationary value across the sweep; the O3 curve at 30 min captures the j_11 sensitivity of the net O3 photoproduction and is the canonical readout the bead acceptance asks for. Window choice is a wall-time/equilibration trade-off (mdl-1yv): longer windows than 30 min cost a near-proportional amount more wall in solve_ivp without materially changing the curve shape.",
                    "time_span": {
                        "start": 0,
                        "end": 1800
                    },
                    "initial_state": {
                        "type": "per_variable",
                        "values": {
                            "NO": 10,
                            "NO2": 20,
                            "O3": 70,
                            "ISOP": 2,
                            "OH": 4e-06,
                            "HO2": 4e-06,
                            "SO2": 1e-09,
                            "SALAAL": 1e-09,
                            "SALCAL": 1e-09
                        }
                    },
                    "parameters": {
                        "T": 298.0,
                        "num_density": 40.896894217403165
                    },
                    "parameter_sweep": {
                        "type": "cartesian",
                        "dimensions": [
                            {
                                "parameter": "j_11",
                                "values": [
                                    0.0,
                                    0.001,
                                    0.0025,
                                    0.005,
                                    0.0075,
                                    0.01,
                                    0.0149,
                                    0.02
                                ]
                            }
                        ]
                    },
                    "plots": [
                        {
                            "id": "OH_vs_jNO2",
                            "type": "line",
                            "description": "Quasi-steady-state OH at t=1800 s vs NO2 photolysis rate j_11.",
                            "x": {
                                "variable": "j_11",
                                "label": "j_11 (1/s)"
                            },
                            "y": {
                                "variable": "OH",
                                "label": "OH (ppb)"
                            }
                        },
                        {
                            "id": "O3_vs_jNO2",
                            "type": "line",
                            "description": "O3 at t=1800 s vs NO2 photolysis rate j_11 — quasi-steady-state ozone response across the dark-to-noon photolysis range.",
                            "x": {
                                "variable": "j_11",
                                "label": "j_11 (1/s)"
                            },
                            "y": {
                                "variable": "O3",
                                "label": "O3 (ppb)"
                            }
                        }
                    ]
                },
                {
                    "id": "temperature_sweep",
                    "description": "Tropospheric-temperature sensitivity at fixed polluted-urban composition and noon photolysis (j_11=0.0149 1/s). Sweeps T across the same 9-grid superfast uses (240 K cold upper-troposphere \u2192 320 K warm boundary layer) and integrates each grid point for 1800 s (30 min \u2014 long enough for the slow O3 budget to respond), then plots the t=1800 s OH and O3 against T. The bimolecular Arrhenius rates and termolecular falloff rates that dominate the HOx, NOx and O3 budgets all carry strong T dependence; the 30-min window lets the net effect on tropospheric O3 emerge in a single curve. Note: num_density is held at 40.9 mol/m\u00b3 (the polluted_urban value) rather than scaling with T at fixed P, so the sweep isolates the rate-coefficient T dependence from the P/T density dependence.",
                    "time_span": {
                        "start": 0,
                        "end": 1800
                    },
                    "initial_state": {
                        "type": "per_variable",
                        "values": {
                            "NO": 10,
                            "NO2": 20,
                            "O3": 70,
                            "ISOP": 2,
                            "OH": 4e-06,
                            "HO2": 4e-06,
                            "SO2": 1e-09,
                            "SALAAL": 1e-09,
                            "SALCAL": 1e-09
                        }
                    },
                    "parameters": {
                        "j_11": 0.0149,
                        "num_density": 40.896894217403165
                    },
                    "parameter_sweep": {
                        "type": "cartesian",
                        "dimensions": [
                            {
                                "parameter": "T",
                                "values": [
                                    240,
                                    250,
                                    260,
                                    270,
                                    280,
                                    290,
                                    300,
                                    310,
                                    320
                                ]
                            }
                        ]
                    },
                    "plots": [
                        {
                            "id": "OH_vs_T",
                            "type": "line",
                            "description": "Quasi-steady-state OH at t=1800 s vs temperature T.",
                            "x": {
                                "variable": "T",
                                "label": "Temperature (K)"
                            },
                            "y": {
                                "variable": "OH",
                                "label": "OH (ppb)"
                            }
                        },
                        {
                            "id": "O3_vs_T",
                            "type": "line",
                            "description": "O3 at t=1800 s vs temperature T — quasi-steady-state ozone response across the cold-troposphere-to-warm-boundary-layer range.",
                            "x": {
                                "variable": "T",
                                "label": "Temperature (K)"
                            },
                            "y": {
                                "variable": "O3",
                                "label": "O3 (ppb)"
                            }
                        }
                    ]
                }
            ],
            "reference": {
                "notes": "source_ref: GasChem.jl src/geoschem_fullchem.jl\nGEOS-Chem fullchem gas-phase mechanism (~819 reactions, ~272 species). Migrated from GasChem.jl GEOSChemGasPhase via mtk2esm with sub-system rate-law inlining.\n\nPost-process workarounds applied (mdl-ode):\n  - 64 max(expr, 0.0) rate clamps were rewritten to (a + abs(a))/2 by scripts/migrations/rewrite_max_in_esm.py because EarthSciSerializationCatalystExt._esm_to_symbolic does not accept the max op. File a follow-on bead in EarthSciSerialization to add max/min support and drop this stop-gap (same lifecycle as scripts/migrations/post_process_geoschem_fullchem.py).\n\nInline tests (mdl-ode): 3 pinned reference states (clean troposphere / polluted urban / upper troposphere) with expected species values from upstream GasChem.GEOSChemGasPhase via mtkcompile + Rosenbrock23. Generator: scripts/migrations/reference_values_geoschem_fullchem.jl. Cross-implementation tolerance rel=1e-3 (loose enough to absorb solver-tolerance and Catalyst path divergence between rxn_sys=false and the migrated flat ReactionSystem; tight enough to catch translation bugs). Reference timing on the workspace machine: GasChem build (rxn_sys=false, ODE-model path) = 1138 s, mtkcompile = 65.6 s, peak RSS during build ~8.2 GiB \u2014 inside the bead's combined 60-min / 32-GiB budget. The migration kept num_density (mol/m\u00b3) but not P; tests override num_density = P / (R_GAS \u00b7 T) per state to maintain (T, P) consistency with the bead-pinned states."
            },
